Avoid mixing magical and mundane items, and be cautious when filtering magical liquids.

message: Start by using the 'vial' tool to extract solid ingredients, especially magical ones. The most reliable high-value combinations came from mixing one magical liquid/extract with one mundane liquid/extract. Avoid combining more than two items, as this often led to a value of 0 for me. Filtering liquids can be useful, but sometimes results in 'poorly-filtered' items. I didn't find a good use for gas ingredients.

Often, the initial combination will have a very negative value, but filtering it immediately afterwards can turn it into a high positive value. Filtering single extracts typically results in 'poorly-filtered' items, which are harder to salvage. Don't re-filter items that already have a good value, as it rarely improves them.

message: Focus on creating extracts from solid ingredients using the ğŸ§ª vial; this reliably yields items with a value of 30. The ğŸ§« filter tool generally degrades items, adding 'botched filtering' and reducing value. The best combinations are often a 'magical' extract with a 'mundane' extract, especially those mentioned in previous hints (like 'unicorn + rose' or 'basilisk + batwing'), which can reach 70-100 value. Combining more than two ingredients, or items with existing 'botched' features, usually leads to negative values. The vial can sometimes refine a combined item if it includes a solid, turning a negative value into a positive one (e.g., -70 to 60), but this is risky on already complex or liquid-only mixtures.
